PlantUML  extension to see the .puml files


ALT + D will render them

steps to follow to make it render properly:

Install latest plantuml:


mkdir -p ~/tools/plantuml
cd ~/tools/plantuml
curl -L -o plantuml.jar https://github.com/plantuml/plantuml/releases/latest/download/plantuml.jar


alias plantuml="java -jar ~/tools/plantuml/plantuml.jar"


Install Graph

https://gitlab.com/graphviz/graphviz/-/releases  ( Source code(tar.gz) download )

mkdir -p ~/tools/graphviz
tar -xzf graphviz-*.tar.gz -C ~/tools/graphviz --strip-components=1

echo 'export PATH=$HOME/tools/graphviz/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc


in Settings -> Extensions -> PlantUML change PlantUML jar to point out to the folder where you extracted aka (home/username/tools/plantium/plantium.jar)